race.comment: EXTOL (8) is third-up and ready to fire back in grade. Has the handy 2kg claim and maps for a soft run. It's hard to risk the Currie barn around here. PORRISTA (9) peaks out of the same race and would be a hope for Currie if she puts her best foot forward. Has Downey on replacing the apprentice and will get every chance from an inside barrier. ELLTITUDE (10) is lightly raced and can build on the Warwick Maiden win. Has the winkers on for the first time and Bayliss replaces the 3kg apprentice. BANDIT (1) went well enough two back to consider.
